content.description: This cool route goes to a small, fine summit.
content.protection: Three bolts protects face climbing to the summit. Double bolts on top to rap off.
content.location: This route is located on the South face of Monkey Dome, and you have to scramble and/or climb up aways to get to the Praying Monkey before you even start the route.  This is the left most route on the south face of Monkey Dome

climbs.name: The Pink Dolphin
climbs.fa: Todd Gordon, John Morales, Amy, Susan, Kim, Karen, Brian

content.description: This route climbs an arete past 3 bolts, and is located right of Elvis Impersonators face climb.
content.protection: Some natural gear and 3 bolts up the arete.
content.location: Right of Elvis Impersonators face pitch, and goes up an arete past 3 bolts.

climbs.name: Elvis Impersonators and Traveling Priests
climbs.fa: Todd Gordon, Cyndie Bransford, Norm Miller

content.description: This cool route goes up the middle of the south face of Monkey Dome, slab climbing up the face past 5 bolts to a 2 bolt anchor.
content.protection: Maybe a sling on a spike if you wish at the start, then it's quick draws only to the anchor.
content.location: Middle of the South face of Monkey Dome

climbs.name: Doctor, Doctor, Doctor
climbs.fa: Brian Povolny, Bill Povolny, Brandt Allen, Todd Gordon

content.description: This is a 2 pitch climb on the right side of the south face of Monkey Dome.  There is one bolt on this climb. Mostly crack climbing.
content.protection: Take a decent sized rack of all sizes, and one QD to clip the one bolt with.
content.location: Far right side of the south face of Monkey Dome.
